<TITLE> Zimbabwe`s Mugabe hands key ministries to his party </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Harare,Oct 11 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe has allocated to his ruling party the ministries of defence, home affairs and finance under a power-sharing deal with the opposition, a government notice seen by Reuters said on Saturday. The main opposition Movement for Democratic Change (MDC) rejected the move, branding it unilateral and said it threatened a power-sharing deal agreed with Mugabe on Sept. 15. The move by Mugabe follows a face-to-face meeting with MDC leader Morgan Tsvangirai during which they agreed to call back talks facilitator South Africa's Thabo Mbeki after a deadlock on the allocation of key ministries
